==Delivering the talisman==
===Talking to Archmage Sedridor===
* '''Archmage Sedridor:''' Welcome adventurer, to the world renowned Wizards' Tower, home to the Order of Wizards. We are the oldest and most prestigious group of wizards around. Now, how may I help you?
* '''Player:''' Are you Sedridor?
* '''Archmage Sedridor:''' Sedridor? What is it you want with him?
* '''Player:''' The Duke of Lumbridge sent me to find him. I have this talisman he found. He said Sedridor would be interested in it.
* '''Archmage Sedridor:''' Did he now? Well hand it over then, and we'll see what all the hubbub is about.
* {{tselect|Select an option}}
* {{topt|Okay, here you are.}}
** '''Player:''' Okay, here you are.
** {{tcond|If the player has the talisman:}}
*** {{tbox|pic=Air talisman detail.png|You hand the talisman to Sedridor.}}
*** '''Archmage Sedridor:''' Hmm... Doesn't seem to be anything too special. Just a normal air talisman by the looks of things. Still, looks can be deceiving. Let me take a closer look...
*** {{tbox|pic=Air talisman detail.png|Sedridor murmurs some sort of incantation and the talisman glows slightly.}}
*** '''Archmage Sedridor:''' How interesting... It would appear I spoke too soon. There's more to this talisman than meets the eye. In fact, it may well be the last piece of the puzzle.
*** '''Player:''' Puzzle?
*** '''Archmage Sedridor:''' Indeed! The lost legacy of the first tower. This talisman may in fact be key to finding the forgotten essence mine!
*** '''Player:''' First tower? Forgotten essence mine? What are you on about?
*** '''Archmage Sedridor:''' Ah, my apologies, adventurer. Allow me to fill you in.
*** {{tselect|Select an option}}
*** {{topt|Go ahead.}}
**** '''Player:''' Go ahead.
**** '''Archmage Sedridor:''' As you are likely aware, when we cast spells, we do so using the power of runes.
**** '''Archmage Sedridor:''' These runes are crafted from a highly unique material, and then imbued with magical power from various runic altars. Different altars create different runes with different magical effects.
**** '''Archmage Sedridor:''' The process of imbuing runes is called runecrafting. Legend has it that this was once a common art, but the secrets of how to do it were lost until just under two hundred years ago.
**** '''Archmage Sedridor:''' The rediscovery of runecrafting had such a large impact on the world, that it marked the dawn of the Fifth Age. It also resulted in the birth of our order, and the construction of the first Wizards' Tower.
**** '''Player:''' If it was the first tower, I'm guessing it doesn't exist anymore? What happened?
**** '''Archmage Sedridor:''' It was burnt down by traitorous members of our own order. They followed the evil god of chaos, Zamorak, and they wished to claim our magical discoveries in his name.
**** '''Archmage Sedridor:''' When the tower burnt down, much was lost, including an important incantation. A spell that could be used to teleport to a hidden essence mine.
**** '''Player:''' The essence mine you mentioned earlier, I assume?
**** '''Archmage Sedridor:''' Precisely. Rune essence is the material used to make runes, but it is incredibly rare. That essence mine was the only place it could be found that our order knew of.
**** '''Archmage Sedridor:''' Since the incantation was lost, we have struggled to maintain our stocks of rune essence.
**** '''Archmage Sedridor:''' There are seemingly those out there that still know where to find some, but while they have been willing to sell essence to us, they have refused to share knowledge on how to find it ourselves.
**** '''Player:''' I'm starting to see why this is so important. So you think this talisman can help you rediscover that incantation?
**** '''Archmage Sedridor:''' I do! All magic leaves traces, and from what I can tell, this talisman was used heavily during the time of the first tower.
**** '''Archmage Sedridor:''' It would have been taken to the essence mine many times, and the magical energies there will have left an imprint on it. To think that it was hidden in Lumbridge all this time!
**** '''Player:''' So what happens now?
**** '''Archmage Sedridor:''' It is critical I share this discovery with my associate, Aubury, as soon as possible. He's not much of a wizard, but he's an expert on runecrafting, and his insight will be essential.
**** '''Archmage Sedridor:''' Would you be willing to visit him for me? I would go myself, but I wish to study this talisman some more.
**** {{tselect|Select an option}}
**** {{topt|Yes, certainly.}}
***** '''Player:''' Yes, certainly.
***** '''Archmage Sedridor:''' He runs a rune shop in the south east of Varrock. Please, take this package of research notes to him. If all goes well, the secrets of the essence mine may soon be ours once more!
***** {{tbox|pic=Research package detail.png|Sedridor hands you a package.}}
***** '''Archmage Sedridor:''' Best of luck, [player name].
***** {{tcond|If the player gave the talisman to him while doubting his identity:}}
****** {{tact|end}}
***** {{tcond|If the player gave the talisman to him without doubting his identity:}}
****** '''Player:''' I don't remember telling you my name... How do you know it?
****** '''Archmage Sedridor:''' Really now? I am the Archmage you know.
****** {{tact|end}}
**** {{topt|No, I'm busy.}}
***** '''Player:''' No, I'm busy.
***** '''Archmage Sedridor:''' As you wish adventurer. I will continue to study this talisman you have brought me. Return here if you find yourself with some spare time to help me.
***** {{tact|end}}
*** {{topt|Actually, I'm not interested.}}
**** '''Player:''' Actually, I'm not interested.
**** '''Archmage Sedridor:''' Oh... Well I guess the short of it is that this talisman could be key to helping us rediscover an important teleportation incantation.
**** '''Archmage Sedridor:''' With it, we'll be able to access a hidden essence mine, our lost source of rune essence.
**** '''Archmage Sedridor:''' It is critical I share this discovery with my associate, Aubury, as soon as possible. He's not much of a wizard, but he's an expert on runecrafting, and his insight will be essential.
**** '''Archmage Sedridor:''' Would you be willing to visit him for me? I would go myself, but I wish to study this talisman some more.
**** {{topt|Yes, certainly.}}
***** {{tact|above}}
**** {{topt|No, I'm busy.}}
***** {{tact|above}}
** {{tcond|If the player does not have the talisman:}}
*** '''Player:''' Okay, here you are.
*** '''Archmage Sedridor:''' ...
*** '''Player:''' ...
*** '''Archmage Sedridor:''' Well?
*** '''Player:''' I don't seem to have it with me.
*** '''Archmage Sedridor:''' Hmm? You are a very odd person. Come back again when you have it.
*** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|No, I'll only give it to Sedridor.}}
** '''Player:''' No, I'll only give it to Sedridor.
** '''Archmage Sedridor:''' Well good news, for I am Sedridor! Now, hand it over and let me have a proper look at it, hmm?
** {{topt|Okay, here you are.}}
*** {{tact|above}}
** {{topt|No, I don't think you are Sedridor.}}
*** '''Player:''' No, I don't think you are Sedridor.
*** '''Archmage Sedridor:''' Hmm... Well, I admire your caution adventurer. Perhaps I can prove myself? I will use my mental powers to discover...
*** '''Archmage Sedridor:''' Your name is... [player name]!
*** '''Player:''' You're right! How did you know that?
*** '''Archmage Sedridor:''' Well I am the Archmage you know! You don't get to my position without learning a few tricks along the way!
*** '''Archmage Sedridor:''' So now that I have proved myself to you, why don't you hand over that talisman, hmm?
*** '''Player:''' Okay, here you are.
*** {{tact|above}}

